{
  "narration": "The final blow cleaves through the mimic's writhing, glistening flesh; its monstrous jaws gape wide in a soundless scream before the creature collapses into a puddle of sticky, acidic ooze. The unnatural stillness that follows is broken only by the faint crackle of blue witchlight in the sconces. Phantom servants, startled and uncertain, fade back to the periphery, their ritual interrupted, and the spectral feast dissolves into mist.\n\nYour breath comes in ragged bursts, your wounds burning from where the mimic's acid and pseudopods struck true. Yet you stand victorious, your sword slick with ichor, the threat to the Great Hall ended. Among the mimic's remains, you spot the glint of treasure it had once guarded: Lord Vael's signet ring, set with a crimson gem and marked by the Vael crest, lies half-embedded in the viscous remains. Nearby, an enchanted goblet shimmers faintly, untouched by the mimic's acid. A jeweled ceremonial dagger and a thick, dust-choked tome--the Family Chronicle--also emerge from the ooze, each artifact steeped in the keep's history and sorrow.\n\nAs you claim these treasures, you feel the attention of the Spectral Scribe upon you and sense the hall's atmosphere shift: the path to the Lord's Study may now be open, provided you possess the signet ring. Your wounds throb, but the weight of hard-earned victory steels your resolve. What do you do next? Tend your wounds, examine your new discoveries, or press onward to the study where Elen's trail and deeper answers await?",
